The paper presents a framework for supervised neural networks that focuses on inducing independence to nuisance factors of data and removing biasing factors from the latent embedding for making fair predictions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
